The White House said President Reaganhad made no decision on whether to reappoint Paul Volcker aschairman of the Federal Reserve Board when Volcker's termexpires in August.    "No decision has been made on chairman Volcker ... He hasnot discussed this with the president, and no decision has beenmade one way or another," White House spokesman Marlin Fitzwatersaid.    Asked if Reagan would discuss the issue with Volcker beforeleaving for the Venice summit on Wednesday, Fitzwater said, "Ihave no idea." Reuter&#3;